"Now there's a wall between us, somethin' there's been lost<br />
I took too much for granted, got my signals crossed." <br />
He is saying that man has lost touch with all of the gifts mother nature provides us. If man pays attention all that we need to be confortable is provided by nature. Shelter in wood, warmth in fire, comfort in a spiritual sense. I dont have time to list all of the clues but just think about it.				
