				<strong class="title">General Comment</strong>I've been through dozens of possible variations of meanings on this song, and all but one are obvious.  My friend once posed an alternate possibility:  that this song is about a soldier in the Vietnam War and a Vietnamese prostitute.  If you take a look at the lyrics, this makes sense for most of the verses, and certainly the overall feel of the song in its original recording on Blood on the Tracks.  What do you all think?				
